column5: Got to camp and saw this.. just about had a heart attack... it fell in exactly the only direction it could have not to demolish something... at least i wint have to go far for cordwood.    and of course we got fishing and she does this to me... again...    Oh well todays a new day.    Its a beautiful day today.. get out there.
Nice pike.  Looks like you still got that horseshoe up yer arse after seeing how that tree fell buddy
Obviously i could care less about your property TJ...cuz the first thing I thought when i saw the first pic was..."good firewood".   Nice pike the missus got there

She got two more small ones today, dammitt    Thats the difference between a man and a woman.. Monique was a bit shocked for a while.. i looked at it said... no damage, i was gonna cut it down any way.. looks like firewood for the fall.. win win for me!!

Musta been windy at some point. Skin it, cut it up in 16" knotless lengths, let them dry and we'll make some baits. As for my sweetie, we have room for her on team#1. Glad you're getting out and about and thanks for the pics.
Got that done yet,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,, Oh wait,yer da BOSS.
Dang lucky you were not there when tha came down. Awesome Pike too. Glad to see i'm not the only one who handles pike with gloves
Bet you that will take a few wobbly-pops to cut and split, no to mention all the time required to sit and watch it dry!
